@NODE hist "Program History"



After Version 4.6 i had a fatal hard drive crash and did not have
any backups, so i lost ALL my source codes for my programs.

Because AmIRSay is being used by a few ppl i decided to
Completely re-write it.


Terminology (what i mean when i say...)

Crash = Program crashes but system is ok.
Guru  = Program crashes and computer resets.

Bugs  = Minor problems

Enforcer hits = Enforcer/Mungwall and Sushi combine to
                monitor a program for illegal memory access
                plus other errors that you do not see as the
                program seems to work ok. a "hit" is an error
                reported by this utility.



The History of AmIRSay from version 5.0b and up
-----------------------------------------------


6.0 AbandonWare
---------------

     This version has the registration stuff removed.

This program is now AbandonWare.
Do what you want to with it.

The only RULE is not to overwrite this version from aminet.

Enjoy.




5.6 FINAL
---------

only a couple of minor changes for the final version.

i think it's prety much working ok now so i'm stopping ALL
developement of AmIRSay from now V 5.6 (22 Feb 2001)

This is because i want to continue AmiSay (not AmIRSay)

If you do not know, AmiSay is like AmIRSay but works with
anything that has a way to send ARexx commands.
Including defaults for AmIRC, StrICQ and YAM :)


