@NODE req "What is Needed ?"

Requirements

For Accents to work you MUST get the following archives from Aminet..

Note: Press to get them from uk.aminet.net (Needs OpenURL.library)

@{" util/libs/translator42.lha " RXS "call addlib('openurl.library',3,-66); call OpenURL('http://uk.aminet.net/pub/aminet/util/libs/translator42.lha', SHOW, TOFRONT, LAUNCH)"} <mbarlow\@pacific.telebyte.net>
@{" util/libs/Tran43pch.lha    " RXS "call addlib('openurl.library',3,-66); call OpenURL('http://uk.aminet.net/pub/aminet/util/libs/Tran43pch.lha', SHOW, TOFRONT, LAUNCH)"} Francesco Devitt <ffranc\@comp.vuw.ac.nz>
@{" util/sys/SayV43.lha        " RXS "call addlib('openurl.library',3,-66); call OpenURL('http://uk.aminet.net/pub/aminet/util/sys/SayV43.lha', SHOW, TOFRONT, LAUNCH)"} Peter Kaltstein <CyberStrike\@studbox.uni-stuttgart.de>

Installation/Upgrading to these is Simple :)

you just put Say in sys:utilities (or something)
then use the translator42.lha Install Script to install translator.library
then use the Tran43pch.lha Installer Script to update translator.library

IMPORTANT: When Installing the new 'Say' command
           make sure the old 'Say' command is removed or replaced.


OTHERWISE you will have to use the 'Say' Package that comes with WB2.x Disks

ABSOLUTELY REQUIRED files are ..
--------------------------------
  narrator.device    (only available on Amiga OS2.x Disks)
  translator.library (on OS.2x Disks or newer versions on Aminet)
  the 'Say' command  (on OS.2x Disks or newer versions on Aminet)


@ENDNODE

@NODE feat "AmIRSay Features"

Features..

 o typed word/s can be spoken as other words , like 'oic' as 'oh i see'
   single words can be omited or any occurence of some text.

 o letters/words/sentences can be blanked (unspoken), like '<' '*' 'f++k'

 o Whole lines can be ignored if they are not normal PRIVMSG's
   like PING, CTCP, SOUND, ect

 o Friends (and enemies) can be given alternative voice styles or can
   be made silent with the 'No Voice' setting.

 o Set a default voice for any nicknames not specified (can be 'No Voice')

 o Simple to use GUI for altering Voice Styles.

 o Easily disable/enable speech for channels just by typing /say#

 o Supports Translator43.library with Accents.

 o Sentences spoken can be prefixed with users nickname.

 o Double Starting in an AmIRC port can be set to either alert you
   that it's already running or it can load the prefs.

 o Online Update Feature to check for and download new versions.

 o OpenURL.library Menus for going to my website and AmIRC


More features may be added in the future

Watch this space :^)

@ENDNODE


@NODE usag "Using AmIRSay"

Using AmIRSay
-------------

AmIRSay comes in 2 main parts.

The First is the AmIRSay.amirx ARexx Script.
This goes in AmIRC/Rexx.
It waits for text processes it and then uses
Amigas 'Say' command to speak it.


The Second is the @{"AmIRSayPrefs mui app" link prfs}
This goes in the AmIRC/  Program dir.
this is a nice gui for altering the configuration of AmIRSay


both utilities have their own Arexx ports with their own commands

When using the AmIRSay_Install Script you can add a few @{" ALIAS " link alias} commands
to AmIRC .


@ENDNODE

@NODE prfs "Using the Prefs Program"

the prefs program AmIRSayPrefs can be used to
edit many of AmIRSays features.

To start it from the channel type  @{" /SAYG " link sayg}
To start it from WB just Double Click it's icon

if amirsay is running and you have the setting for double starting
set to load the prefs program then you can use /says again
or use 'AmIRSay.amirx' in AmIRCs menu again.

@{"Features Of the Prefs Program.."  LINK feat}

@ENDNODE


@NODE says "Starting AmIRSay"

You can Start AmIRSay in many ways...

               in a channel type /rx amirsay ..

1 argument can be parsed -a<bool> . this is to override the setting for
letting all the channel users you have started AmIRSay.

i use it if i have a newer version than than my friends as it normaly
only outputs the text to me and i don't want to have to redo the settings

eg..
/says -a0  ; this will output to only you no matter what your settings
/says -a1  ; this will output to the channel no matter what your settings

---------

or select the AmIRC Arexx menu 'AmIRSay.amirx'
or if you installed the aliases then type /says


------------------

AutoStarting AmIRSay.
---------------------

here is a handy thing to do.

have AmIRSay Start whenever you connect to a server :)

howto:

Create or Edit a file in AmIRC/rexx/ called Connected.amirx
IMPORTANT: ARexx files MUST have "/* */" in the first line.

add the following text to the file...


/* Begin AutoStart AmIRSay */
 portnumber=right(address(),1)
 if ~show('p','AMIRSAYRX.'portnumber) then 'say /rx amirsay'
/* End AutoStart AmIRSay */


@ENDNODE

@NODE sayv "Getting the version number"

You can Get the version string of AmIRSay in these ways...

               in a channel type /rx amirsay sayv ..

or if you installed the aliases then type /sayv

@ENDNODE

@NODE sayn "Check and download new version"

You can Check for new versions online and download them ...

               in a channel type /rx amirsay sayn ..

or if you installed the aliases then type /sayn


For this to work you must be online and have valid TCP: access

Programs like nc2 , AmiTCP, Miami, Genesis should be ok

@ENDNODE

@NODE sayg "load the Prefs GUI"

You can Start AmIRSayPrefs in many ways...

In a channel type /rx amirsay sayg ..

or if you installed the aliases then type /sayg


If AmIRSay.amirx is already running in your AmIRC port
then you can either..

get a message saying it's already running

or make it load AmIRSayPrefs
@ENDNODE


@NODE sayu "Updating Settings"

this is pretty obsolete now as the prefs program will apply this
command when you save the settings.

i kept it in for people who might edit their settings
by hand and need a way to reload.

this command (and a couple of others) will ping to the server before running.

the reason for this is that the AmIRSay.amirx script is locked while waiting
for someone to say something. A ping will cause the lock to be freed.

@ENDNODE

@NODE sayq "Quitting"
@ENDNODE

@NODE say# "Ignoring Channels"

This will toggle on/off speaking in a given channel.

The permanent list can be edited in the @{"prefs page" link prfs}

Syntax:

'SAY# <CHANNEL>' if CHANNEL is not given the current channel is used

examples..

/say#        ; Silence/Hear current channel

/say# peecee ; Toggle #peecee channel


2 other args are avaiable..

'SAY# L' Lists the channels Currently being ignored

'SAY# S' saves any changes to channel ignoring


@ENDNODE

@NODE say? "Calling Help"
@ENDNODE

@NODE alias "Aliases added by Install_AmIRSay"

Using the Install script has a function to add some handy alases to amirc

Don't wory if you already have them because they will all be updated

All alias commands are typed in an AmIRC channel window...

Selecting Yes to adding these aliases gives the following commands

/SAYS = @{" Start AmIRSay         " link says} Starts the script and monitors channels
/SAYV = @{" Get AmIRSay Version   " link sayv} gives you the version of your AmIRSay
/SAYN = @{" Check for New Version " link sayn} Downloads newer version (if any)
/SAYG = @{" load GUI              " link sayg} starts the prefs program (or activates it)
/SAYU = @{" Update Preferences    " link sayu} reloads settings if edited by hand
/SAYQ = @{" QUIT AmIRSay          " link sayq} Exits the ARexx script
/SAY# = @{" Ignoring Channels     " link say#} Turn Speaking off/on in a channel
/SAY? = @{" Call Help             " link say?} Lists these commands.

@ENDNODE

@NODE inst "How to install"

installation

Manual:
AmIRSay.amirx must be in AmIRC/Rexx/ dir
AmIRSayPrefs must be in AmIRC/ dir
AmIRSay.guide can be in AmIRC/ or HELP: or HELP:English/

Running the install script:

Double click the Install icon

Follow the prompts.

Tip: Allways choose to add the Aliases to AmIRC config
     as they may have changed.


-------------------------------

Notes:

     if AmIRC is running quit and restart to activate the menuitem or type

                      @{b}@{u}/rx amirsay@{uu}@{ub} in the channel window



               to test if "say" works on your Amiga just use the
                   Workbench menu 'Execute Command' and enter

                                 say something

    if you hear the word something spoken you are ok . if not
      check you have the translator.library in libs: and the
  narrator.device in devs: and say in sys:utilities or something


@ENDNODE

@NODE arex "AmIRSay ARexx port AMIRSAYPREFS"


              AmIRSay Creates an ARexx port called "AMIRSAYPREFS"

           It has all the Standard command that come with any MUI app
                          like 'SHOW' and 'QUIT' ect.

to see all commands in ANY MUI Application try executing
something like this command in a shell..

@{fg highlight}rx "address AMIRSAYPREFS 'HELP Ram:AmIRSay_RX.hlp'"@{fg text}

then take a look at Ram:AmIRSay_RX.hlp


Command      Template
-------      --------
quit         FORCE/S  ; Exits Application
hide       .........  ; Iconifies
deactivate .........  ; Commodity De-Activation
show       .........  ; Un-Iconify
activate   .........  ; Commodity Activation
info         ITEM/A   ; shows app info ITEM can be..
                       TITLE ; App Title
                     VERSION ; Version String
                      AUTHOR ; Author
                        BASE ; ARexx Port
                   COPYRIGHT ; Copyright
                 DESCRIPTION ; description

help         FILE/A   ; prints ARexx commands to FILE


                          ----------------------------


Currently there are only 2 Extra Command Added

TOFRONT  ; Un-Iconifies (if needed) and brings window to front

UPDATE   ; Starts the OnLine Update Process


You can use the port in many ways.

As an AmIRC Alias (note: the '"' quotes)

 /alias sayIcon = /rx "address AMIRSAYPREFS 'HIDE'"
 /alias showsay = /rx "address AMIRSAYPREFS 'TOFRONT'"
 /alias sayqgui = /rx "address AMIRSAYPREFS 'QUIT'"

-----------
In an ARexx Script.

 address AMIRSAYPREFS
 HIDE
 TOFRONT
 QUIT

-----------
as a DOS command in a launcher or something.

 sys:rexxc/rx "address AMIRSAYPREFS 'HIDE'"
 sys:rexxc/rx "address AMIRSAYPREFS 'TOFRONT'"
 sys:rexxc/rx "address AMIRSAYPREFS 'QUIT'"


@ENDNODE

@NODE cata "Catalog Support"

AmIRSay has FULL Catalog support (i think;)

At the moment français, deutsch, and dansk are present but
are salvaged from the old AmIRSay (before i lost the source)

some strings are missing (currently in english)



Many Thanks to these people for adding their languages...

Italiano.catalog . @{" Giacomo Mazzullo " RXS "call addlib('openurl.library',3,-66); call OpenURL('mailto:giacmazz@yiscalinet.it', SHOW, TOFRONT, LAUNCH)"}





How to add catalogs for your own language.
------------------------------------------

PLEASE READ THIS...

The method used by me is using a program found on Aminet called SimpleCat

get SimpleCat from aminet and put it in your c: dir
@{" Click here to Download SimpleCat " RXS "call addlib('openurl.library',3,-66); call OpenURL('http://uk.aminet.net/pub/aminet/dev/misc/simplecat.lha', SHOW, TOFRONT, LAUNCH)"}


SimpleCat is very easy to use as all args are already set in the .cs file

the '.cs' files are the descriptor files for use with SimpleCat.

languages are defined on the first line seperated by commas ','

eg.
## languages english,deutsch,espańol

then the Locale Strings are defined by line and seperated by ';'
eg.

;
MSG_YES
_Yes
_Ya
_Si
;
MSG_HELLO
Hello
Hallo
Bonjour


it is best to edit the catalogs in the original archive Catalog dir.
I have included a little dos script that will run SimpleCat
(SimpleCat MUST be in your path eg. C:SimpleCat)



RULES:
------

PLEASE TRY TO STICK TO THESE RULES IN MAKING TRANSLATIONS...
------------------------------------------------------------

Please Please try to keep all texts to a similar length
larger texts will affect the sizes of the gui/gadgets and requesters

if possible use 'WELL KNOWN' Abreviations to try to make the gui smaller.

Watch out for the special characters like \\e1 \\ec as they are used by mui
Watch out for _Underscores , ensure you don't repeat keykodes to gadgets


PLEASE Send me your updated ".cs" files and docs (if you made docs),

NO OTHER FILES WILL BE ACCEPTED OR USED

@{" Bruce Steers <bsteers@ukonline.co.uk> " RXS "call addlib('openurl.library',3,-66); call OpenURL('mailto:bsteers@ukonline.co.uk?SUBJECT=AmIRSay Catalogs', SHOW, TOFRONT, LAUNCH)"}


Thanks for reading this Text,
Bruce


-------------------------------------------
ONLY SEND ME EDITED .cs FILES (and/or docs)
-------------------------------------------

I WILL NOT accept any .catalog or any other translation methods.

you are free to upload a catalog to aminet but be aware that if
i add/remove any strings then your catalogs won't work but if
i have the .cs file they will :)

Submitters of languages will have their names Added above :)

@ENDNODE
